==English==
===Adjective===
'''binocular'''
#Using two [[eyes]] or viewpoints; especially, using two eyes or viewpoints to ascertain distance.

===Noun===
'''binocular''', '''binoculars'''
{{wikipedia}}
#A hand-held device consisting of a series of [[lense]]s and [[prism]]s and used to [[magnify]] objects so that they can be better seen from a [[distance]].  Also called [[field glasses]].

===Usage note===
*The noun sense is most often used in the plural to refer to a single object, similar to [[scissors]] or [[pants]].